# Canva Master Guide
**E.I. Werner / Outside Inn Studios | April 2026**
*Verified against live Canva session + canva.com documentation. Last updated: April 2026.*

> **How to use this file:** This is the single reference for all Canva workflows used by E.I. Werner. Add it to your Claude Project and GitHub so any AI assistant has accurate, verified knowledge of Canva's capabilities. Do not give Canva advice without consulting this file first. Features and pricing verified April 2026.

---

## Why Canva (Not Figma)

Canva is the correct tool for EIW's design production. Figma is a layout tool — it cannot apply strokes or drop shadows that follow the actual shape of a person cutout. It always uses the rectangular bounding box. **This has been confirmed by direct testing.** Canva handles person-shaped outlines and shadows natively and correctly, as verified in a live session April 2026.

---

## Primary Use Cases for EIW

1. **YouTube thumbnails** — 1280×720px
2. **OBS lecture slides** — 608×738px (standard B-layout) or 608×1080px (floating cam) — exported as PNG for use as Image sources in OBS
3. **Vertical short-form content** — 1080×1920px for TikTok, Shorts, Reels (future)
4. **Stream graphics** — Twitch overlays, panels, "Starting Soon" screens at 1920×1080px

---

