## Vertical Content Workflow (Short-Form / TikTok / Reels)

### Creating 1080×1920px designs from scratch (free)

1. **canva.com → search "TikTok Video"** or **"Instagram Reel"** — this creates a 1080×1920px canvas automatically
2. Or: **Custom size → 1080 × 1920px**
3. Design on the vertical canvas — all standard Canva tools available
4. Export as **PNG** (static), **JPG** (static), or **MP4** (animated, up to 1080p, up to 30 min on free)

### Repurposing lecture slides to vertical (free plan — manual)

Magic Resize is Pro-only. The free manual workflow:
1. Create a **new** 1080×1920px canvas
2. Open your 608×738px lecture slide in another tab
3. Copy elements and paste into the vertical canvas
4. Rearrange for the vertical format — face/cam zone at top, content zone below
5. Adjust font sizes up (text needs to be larger in the expanded space)

This is the bottleneck on the free plan. When repurposing becomes a regular task, the Pro trial or subscription becomes worth evaluating.

### MP4 video export for vertical clips

Canva can export animated designs as vertical MP4 — useful for creating short video clips from slides with animations. The export respects the design orientation: a 1080×1920 design exports as a 1080×1920 MP4. Free plan: up to 1080p, up to 30 minutes.

