## Brand Consistency on the Free Plan

### What's available free
- 1 Brand Kit with 3 colors and 2 fonts
- Fonts must be chosen from Canva's built-in library (no custom uploads)
- No logo storage, no saved brand templates

### The brand board workaround
Create a Canva document called "EIW Brand Board" containing:
- Your exact hex color codes (copy-paste into the color picker each time)
- Your two font names
- Your logo uploaded as a regular image element
- An example slide showing the correct layout and proportions

Reference this document whenever starting a new design. Enter hex codes manually in the color picker — Canva accepts direct hex input. Use `Ctrl+Alt+C` (copy style) and `Ctrl+Alt+V` (paste style) to propagate consistent text treatment across elements.

### When to upgrade for brand consistency
If you find yourself manually re-entering brand colors and fonts across 20+ designs, or if a hired editor needs consistent brand assets to work from, Pro's full Brand Kit becomes worth the cost. The 30-day trial is the right way to test this.

