## Keyboard Shortcuts

| Action | Shortcut |
|---|---|
| Undo | Ctrl + Z |
| Redo | Ctrl + Shift + Z |
| Duplicate element | Ctrl + D |
| Group elements | Ctrl + G |
| Ungroup | Ctrl + Shift + G |
| Copy | Ctrl + C |
| Paste | Ctrl + V |
| Select all | Ctrl + A |
| Delete element | Delete key |
| Move element (1px) | Arrow keys |
| Move element (10px) | Shift + Arrow keys |
| Zoom in/out | Ctrl + Plus / Minus |
| Fit to screen | Ctrl + Shift + H |
| Add text | T key |
| Copy style | Ctrl + Alt + C |
| Paste style | Ctrl + Alt + V |
| Lock element | Ctrl + Shift + K |

**High-leverage shortcuts for template workflows:**
- `Ctrl+D` — duplicate entire slide/page including all elements. Build one master, duplicate for each myth.
- `Ctrl+Shift+K` — lock background layer before editing foreground content. Prevents accidental moves.
- `Ctrl+Alt+C` / `Ctrl+Alt+V` — copy style, paste style. Get text treatment right once, propagate everywhere.
- `Ctrl+G` — group text + image elements before duplicating to keep layouts locked.

