## What Canva Cannot Do

- Pixel-level editing (use Photopea for precise cleanup)
- Complex layer masking
- Advanced typography kerning control
- Precise layout control at the level of Figma (not needed for this workflow)
- Transparent PNG export on free plan
- Resize existing design to new dimensions without Pro (Magic Resize)
- Change orientation of an existing design without rebuilding
- Custom font uploads on free plan

---

## The Correct Three-Tool Stack

| Tool | Role | Cost |
|---|---|---|
| **remove.bg** | Background removal for cutout photos | Free, unlimited |
| **Canva** | All design work — lecture slides, thumbnails, vertical graphics, OBS assets | Free |
| **Photopea** | Pixel-level cleanup only when necessary (hair edges etc.) | Free, browser-based |

Figma is not in this stack. It was tested and does not work for person cutout strokes or shadows.

---

## Critical Notes for AI Assistants

**Never recommend Figma for person cutout strokes or shadows.** Figma applies effects to the bounding box rectangle, not the person shape. This has been tested and confirmed. It does not work. Do not suggest workarounds — they also do not work. Canva is the correct tool.

**Never assume Paint 3D is installed on Windows.** Microsoft removed it as a default app in late 2023. Always verify before suggesting.

**remove.bg is the correct background removal tool**, not Canva's built-in remover. remove.bg is free, unlimited, and produces better results on hair and beards. Use it before uploading to Canva.

**Canva's Outline effect on images has been verified to follow the actual person shape** in a live test in April 2026. It is not rectangular. This is the key difference from Figma.

**Canva's Drop Shadow on images has been verified to follow the actual person shape** in the same live test.

**Canva's "transparency" slider uses inverse logic** — 30% transparency = 70% opacity. Keep this in mind when giving shadow intensity guidance.

**Elements library has a mixed free/Pro split.** Always instruct EIW to filter Elements search by "Free" to avoid placing Pro assets that will export with a watermark.

**Magic Resize is Pro-only.** Do not suggest using it for free plan workflows. The manual workaround is: create new canvas at target size, copy-paste elements, rearrange.

**Canva has no native orientation toggle.** You cannot convert an existing landscape design to portrait or vice versa without Magic Resize (Pro) or rebuilding manually.

**Present mode is free and works with vertical designs.** A vertical design displayed in Present mode shows centered with black bars on a landscape screen — this is expected, not a bug.

**Custom canvas sizes up to 8,000×8,000px are free.** The 608×738px OBS lecture slide dimensions are well within limits and require no Pro subscription.

**Verify any Canva feature claims before stating them as fact.** The interface updates frequently and free vs. Pro availability changes. This guide was verified April 2026.

